## GAP 1: Pending Handler - Missing QUEUE_COMPLETED Publish for Skipped Tasks

### Go Code (pending.go lines 43-57):
```go
func (h *pendingHandler) skipTask(ctx context.Context, t *tork.Task) error {
	now := time.Now().UTC()
	t.State = tork.TaskStateSkipped
	t.ScheduledAt = &now
	t.StartedAt = &now
	t.CompletedAt = &now
	if err := h.ds.UpdateTask(ctx, t.ID, func(u *tork.Task) error {
		u.State = t.State
		u.ScheduledAt = t.ScheduledAt
		u.StartedAt = t.StartedAt
		return nil
	}); err != nil {
		return errors.Wrapf(err, "error updating task in datastore")
	}
	return h.broker.PublishTask(ctx, broker.QUEUE_COMPLETED, t)  // <-- MISSING IN RUST
}
```

### Rust Code (pending.rs lines 132-147):
```rust
pub async fn handle(&self, ctx: HandlerContext, task: &mut Task) -> Result<(), HandlerError> {
    let decision = evaluate_pending(task);
    match decision {
        PendingDecision::Skip => {
            apply_skip_transition(task, OffsetDateTime::now_utc());
            // MISSING: Publish to QUEUE_COMPLETED via broker
        }
        PendingDecision::Schedule => {
            self.scheduler
                .schedule_task(task)
                .await
                .map_err(|e| HandlerError::Handler(e.to_string()))?;
        }
    }
    (self.handler)(ctx, TaskEventType::StateChange, task)
}
```

### Expected Fix:
After `apply_skip_transition`, the Rust code should publish the skipped task to the completed queue:
```rust
self.broker
    .publish_task(queue::QUEUE_COMPLETED.to_string(), task)
    .await
    .map_err(|e| HandlerError::Broker(e.to_string()))?;
```

